<p><strong style="background-color: #eacf32;">Earnings per Share (EPS)</strong></p>
<p>The earnings per share represent the profitability on a per-share basis. The EPS and PAT growing at a similar rate indicate that the company does not dilute the earnings by issuing new shares, which is good for the existing shareholders. One can think of this as a reflection of the company’s management’s capabilities.</p>
