<p>The 5 year EPS CAGR stands at 1.90% for the FY14.</p>
<p><strong style="background-color: #eacf32;">Gross Profit margins</strong></p>
<p>Gross profit margins, expressed as a percentage is calculated as a –</p>
<p><strong>Gross Profits / Net Sales</strong></p>
<p>Where,</p>
<p>Gross Profits = [Net Sales – Cost of Goods Sold]</p>
<p>Cost of goods sold is the cost involved in making the finished good; we had discussed this calculation while understanding the inventory turnover ratio. Let us proceed to check how ARBL’s Gross Profit margins have evolved over the years.</p>
